do!  A good place to announce your work is the <a href=\"http://lists.ros.org/lurker/list/ros-users.en.html\" target=\"_blank\">ros-users@</a> mailing list.\n</p>\n<div><img style=\"float: left; vertical-align: bottom; margin-top:21px; margin-right: 10px; height: 46px\" alt=\"Tools icon\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/contribute_maintain.png\"><p style=\"display:inline-block\"><h2 class=\"widgettitle\">Maintain Packages</h2></div>\n<p>\nOne of the most important roles in the ROS community is that of package maintainers.  Package maintainers are the people who release packages into specific ROS distributions and verify that they integrate properly. Early in a package\'s lifecycle, the maintainer is usually the original author.  But over time authors move on, potentially leaving valuable code without a maintainer.  This is where a maintainer can pick up a package and take responsibility for keeping it available to the greater ROS community.  Note that maintainership is not a commitment to do new development on a package.  Maintainership can be limited to considering patches for bug fixes and managing releases. With each ROS distribution, a call for maintainership is circulated on the <a href=\"http://lists.ros.org/lurker/list/ros-release.en.html\" target=\"_blank\">ros-release@ </a>mailing list.  If you are interested in becoming a maintainer, please join the ros-release@ list.\n</p>\";}s:6:\"84652f\";a:1:{s:13:\"pl_area_class\";s:21:\"side-navbar-separator\";}}}');
INSERT INTO `wp_postmeta` VALUES (683,99,'pl-settings','a:2:{s:4:\"live\";a:7:{s:13:\"page-template\";s:12:\"rosotherpage\";s:10:\"custom-map\";a:1:{s:8:\"template\";a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"pl_area94dae8\";s:6:\"object\";s:13:\"PLSectionArea\";s:3:\"sid\";s:7:\"pl_area\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"94dae8\";s:7:\"content\";a:2:{i:0;a:7:{s:6:\"object\";s:8:\"PLColumn\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"84652f\";s:3:\"sid\";s:8:\"plcolumn\";s:4:\"span\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:4:\"true\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:\"object\";s:19:\"PageLinesWidgetizer\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"i2d7ua\";s:3:\"sid\";s:10:\"widgetizer\";s:4:\"span\";s:2:\"12\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";}}}i:1;a:7:{s:6:\"object\";s:8:\"PLColumn\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"846636\";s:3:\"sid\";s:8:\"plcolumn\";s:4:\"span\";s:1:\"9\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:\"object\";s:16:\"PageLinesTextBox\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"uhkxqp\";s:3:\"sid\";s:7:\"textbox\";s:4:\"span\";s:2:\"12\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";}}}}}}}s:6:\"13fdwz\";a:8:{s:12:\"navbar_theme\";s:4:\"base\";s:11:\"navbar_menu\";s:1:\"6\";s:19:\"navbar_enable_hover\";s:1:\"0\";s:24:\"navbar_enable_hover-flip\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"navbar_alignment\";s:1:\"0\";s:21:\"navbar_alignment-flip\";s:1:\"0\";s:17:\"navbar_hidesearch\";s:1:\"0\";s:22:\"navbar_hidesearch-flip\";s:1:\"0\";}s:6:\"gequlx\";a:2:{s:15:\"simple_nav_menu\";s:1:\"6\";s:16:\"simple_nav_align\";s:4:\"left\";}s:6:\"i2d7ua\";a:1:{s:15:\"widgetizer_area\";s:13:\"otw-sidebar-5\";}s:6:\"uhkxqp\";a:1:{s:15:\"textbox_content\";s:1769:\"<h2 class=\"widgettitle\">ROSCon</h2>\n<img style=\"float: right; margin: 30px\" alt=\"ROSCon 2013 collage\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/roscon2013-collage.jpg\">\n<p>\nROSCon is the annual ROS developers\' conference.  It’s a chance for ROS developers of all levels, beginner to expert, to spend an extraordinary couple of days learning from and networking with the ROS community.  Attendees get tips and tricks from experts and meet and share ideas with fellow developers from around the globe.\n</p><p>\nPrevious editions of ROSCon include:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2014\" target=\"_blank\">September 2014: Chicago, Illinois </a>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013\" target=\"_blank\">May 2013: Stuttgart, Germany</a>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012\" target=\"_blank\">May 2012: St. Paul, Minnesota</a>\n</ul>\n<p>\nThe usual format of ROSCon is a two-day program comprising technical talks and tutorials that introduce you to new tools and libraries, as well as teach you more about the ones you already know. The bulk of the program is 30-40 minute presentations.  There are also sessions of Lightning Talks, which are 3-minute mini-talks that are scheduled just-in-time at the conference.  And there’s open space at the conference for Birds-of-a-Feather meetings, impromptu hacking sessions, and informal presentations.\n</p><p>\nWe post videos of all the sessions after the conference (e.g., <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2014/program\" target=\"_blank\">2014</a>, <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013/program\" target=\"_blank\">2013</a>, <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012/program\" target=\"_blank\">2012</a>).\n</p><p>\nWe usually hold ROSCon in the fall; For the latest information about ROSCon vist <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org\">roscon.ros.org</a>!\n</p>\";}s:6:\"84652f\";a:1:{s:13:\"pl_area_class\";s:21:\"side-navbar-separator\";}}s:5:\"draft\";a:7:{s:13:\"page-template\";s:12:\"rosotherpage\";s:10:\"custom-map\";a:1:{s:8:\"template\";a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:4:\"name\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"class\";s:0:\"\";s:2:\"id\";s:13:\"pl_area94dae8\";s:6:\"object\";s:13:\"PLSectionArea\";s:3:\"sid\";s:7:\"pl_area\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"94dae8\";s:7:\"content\";a:2:{i:0;a:7:{s:6:\"object\";s:8:\"PLColumn\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"84652f\";s:3:\"sid\";s:8:\"plcolumn\";s:4:\"span\";s:1:\"2\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:4:\"true\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:\"object\";s:19:\"PageLinesWidgetizer\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"i2d7ua\";s:3:\"sid\";s:10:\"widgetizer\";s:4:\"span\";s:2:\"12\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";}}}i:1;a:7:{s:6:\"object\";s:8:\"PLColumn\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"846636\";s:3:\"sid\";s:8:\"plcolumn\";s:4:\"span\";s:1:\"9\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:6:\"object\";s:16:\"PageLinesTextBox\";s:5:\"clone\";s:6:\"uhkxqp\";s:3:\"sid\";s:7:\"textbox\";s:4:\"span\";s:2:\"12\";s:6:\"offset\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"newrow\";s:5:\"false\";}}}}}}}s:6:\"13fdwz\";a:8:{s:12:\"navbar_theme\";s:4:\"base\";s:11:\"navbar_menu\";s:1:\"6\";s:19:\"navbar_enable_hover\";s:1:\"0\";s:24:\"navbar_enable_hover-flip\";s:1:\"0\";s:16:\"navbar_alignment\";s:1:\"0\";s:21:\"navbar_alignment-flip\";s:1:\"0\";s:17:\"navbar_hidesearch\";s:1:\"0\";s:22:\"navbar_hidesearch-flip\";s:1:\"0\";}s:6:\"gequlx\";a:2:{s:15:\"simple_nav_menu\";s:1:\"6\";s:16:\"simple_nav_align\";s:4:\"left\";}s:6:\"i2d7ua\";a:1:{s:15:\"widgetizer_area\";s:13:\"otw-sidebar-5\";}s:6:\"uhkxqp\";a:1:{s:15:\"textbox_content\";s:1769:\"<h2 class=\"widgettitle\">ROSCon</h2>\n<img style=\"float: right; margin: 30px\" alt=\"ROSCon 2013 collage\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/roscon2013-collage.jpg\">\n<p>\nROSCon is the annual ROS developers\' conference.  It’s a chance for ROS developers of all levels, beginner to expert, to spend an extraordinary couple of days learning from and networking with the ROS community.  Attendees get tips and tricks from experts and meet and share ideas with fellow developers from around the globe.\n</p><p>\nPrevious editions of ROSCon include:\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2014\" target=\"_blank\">September 2014: Chicago, Illinois </a>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013\" target=\"_blank\">May 2013: Stuttgart, Germany</a>\n<li><a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012\" target=\"_blank\">May 2012: St. Paul, Minnesota</a>\n</ul>\n<p>\nThe usual format of ROSCon is a two-day program comprising technical talks and tutorials that introduce you to new tools and libraries, as well as teach you more about the ones you already know. The bulk of the program is 30-40 minute presentations.  There are also sessions of Lightning Talks, which are 3-minute mini-talks that are scheduled just-in-time at the conference.  And there’s open space at the conference for Birds-of-a-Feather meetings, impromptu hacking sessions, and informal presentations.\n</p><p>\nWe post videos of all the sessions after the conference (e.g., <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2014/program\" target=\"_blank\">2014</a>, <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2013/program\" target=\"_blank\">2013</a>, <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org/2012/program\" target=\"_blank\">2012</a>).\n</p><p>\nWe usually hold ROSCon in the fall; For the latest information about ROSCon vist <a href=\"http://roscon.ros.org\">roscon.ros.org</a>!\n</p>\";}s:6:\"84652f\";a:1:{s:13:\"pl_area_class\";s:21:\"side-navbar-separator\";}}}');
